  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "DXF ASCII structure: group-code/value pairs — integer code on one line, string/float/int value on next line. Sections delimited by '  0\\nSECTION' / '  0\\nENDSEC'. Section order: HEADER ($ACADVER, $INSBASE, $EXTMIN, $EXTMAX, etc.), CLASSES, TABLES (LAYER, LTYPE, STYLE, APPID, DIMSTYLE, BLOCK_RECORD), BLOCKS, ENTITIES (LINE, ARC, CIRCLE, LWPOLYLINE, INSERT, TEXT, MTEXT, HATCH, DIMENSION, SPLINE, ELLIPSE, 3DFACE, SOLID), OBJECTS, THUMBNAILIMAGE, EOF. Key group codes: 0=entity type, 1=text string, 2=name, 5=handle, 6=linetype, 7=textstyle, 8=layer, 10/20/30=X/Y/Z coord, 38=elevation, 39=thickness, 40-48=doubles, 62=color, 67=space(0=model,1=paper), 100=subclass marker, 330=owner handle. $ACADVER in HEADER section = DWG version code (AC1009-AC1032). Binary DXF: 21-byte header 'AutoCAD Binary DXF\\r\\n\\x1A\\x00' then group codes as 16-bit LE integers.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Bytes 0-3: should be '  0\\r' or '  0\\n' for ASCII DXF; 'Auto' for Binary DXF",
      "Search for '$ACADVER' in HEADER section to find AutoCAD version (AC1009-AC1032)",
      "Count SECTION/ENDSEC pairs to identify present sections (HEADER, TABLES, ENTITIES, etc.)",
      "Check for Binary DXF magic 'AutoCAD Binary DXF\\r\\n\\x1A\\x00' at offset 0 (21 bytes)"
    ]
  },
